For Sale (firm price); A New In The Box (NIB), Hi Point 380 ACP, in this case New In a Hard Plastic Shell with Foam Liner.  This is the two tone 380 ACP hand gun.  The Slide is Black with about a half inch Satin rail going down each side of the Slide.  The Body of all Hi Point hand guns are Black Polymer with plastic grips.  My Friend Bob, just bought a Hi Point 9C, because the frame of the 9C and the 380 ACP are identical.  He really likes the feel of these firearms.  He started out with the 45 ACP and the 40 S&W.  As you can see Bob likes guns.  This could be my story I started with the Hi Point 40 S&W. I purchased a used 9C and it felt great in the hand.  Much more comfortable than the Full Size Hi Point 45 & 40 models.  I love to shoot my Hi Point 40 S&W.  I enjoy it so much I purchased 1,000 rounds of 40 S&W ammo.  The Hi Point 45 is still New In the Box with a Laser.  (Hi Point does make a OD green 40 and 45 hand gun).  I purchased the 380 ACP for my collection; and I can purchase as many as I want, as I am a FFL.  

If you like fun guns like I do, check Morrisonmall.com  Morrisonmall.com has a full LIne of NEW Cobra, NEW Charter Arms Revolvers,  NEW Heritage Revolvers and NEW Hi Point firearms.  All NEW Hi Point, Charter Arms Revolvers, Heritage Revolvers and NEW Cobra hand guns have FREE SHIPPING to your FFL.  If local purchaser (New Mexico resident pickup), I will do the required background check as part of the service for FREE.  So everyone gets something for FREE!  If you do not see it call or email me at REDACTED

As with all firearms and especially with children, you must be very, very vigilant. My neighbor’s child was shooting a 22 training rifle.  This rifle is a one shot 22 lr cal. The boy enjoys shooting 22‘s as they have very little kick and are not very loud.  This was the second time he went shooting.  As a side note, he enjoyed shooting so much, he behaved and listened much more attentively than at other times.  First time out shooting he behaved for over 3 ½ hours, this past time we were out 2 ½ plus hours. At ten years old, I require the boy to read gun safety pamphlets and other similar materials.  I quiz him when he now walks with me and my pit bull.  He was frightened of dogs, but has been overcoming this fear.  Shooting can be a great bonding and educational tool for young teens and children.  Again, much care and caution should be taken. 100 percent attention when all the time a child is with a rifle and more so when a child handles a hand gun.   Even though I cannot shoot as much as I would like, I enjoy the experience of shooting with the child.  (Of Course I get permission from the boys MOM!)

I shot 2 Hi Point 40 S&W’s  which at 10 to 12 yards shot about 3’ to the right of center. All new Hi Points have an adjustable rear sight for even better sight adjustments.  I have not bothered to adjust the rear sight on my 40’s. The up down pattern was less than an inch off a straight line.   These are great inexpensive (affordable) fun hand guns to shoot. title: For Sale:  Night Sight Installation for Semi-Auto Pistols
postcontent:
Service offered for installing night sights onto handguns (semi auto pistols). I can also remove and replace factory sights and target sights as you wish.

For $25 I will remove your old sights and install new night sights, target sights or whatever you provide (or I can source some for you at an additional cost). I can give discounts for multiple guns from same customer.

Most gunsmiths or factories charge $50-$100+ for this service plus the cost of the sights (which they may or may not up charge) and they keep your gun for days or weeks or you have to mail it in and pay shipping/insurance.

You can just bring me your bare slide or I can gladly remove your slide. I can perform this job with a very fast turn around. Usually same day and as fast as a couple of hours.

I perform this service using custom made tooling so the resulting product is clean and properly installed. No punches or hammers involved and I can do it on even the hardest of factory sights like the springfield XD series.

postcontent:
This is a Rock River Arms .204 Ruger Varmint Rifle.  It is a "lights out" shooter with accuracy tighter than 3/4 MOA.  I have personally shot it to 1/2 MOA.

Round Count is 150 rounds, and condition is "as new".  The Upper and Lower were both manufactured and assembled by Rock River Arms.  This is NOT a home build.

This is another "safe queen" that doesn't get taken out very often, and needs to find a home with someone who will put her to good use.  I have two nearly identical rifles in .204 Ruger, and I don't need them both.

This rifle has a 1:12 twist rate that optimally stabilizes 32 grain Hornady AMax bullets.  The buyer should be aware that a 1:12 twist rate is NOT adequate to stabilize 40 grain AMax's.  I have not tried other bullets like the Speer, Nosler, or any other bullet weights or types besides the factory loaded Hornady AMax 32's and 40's.

Rifle Details:

Optics:  Leupold Mark AR 4-12X40 Matte finish 1" tube with MilDot Reticle and .223/55gr. BDC elevation turret.  The Mount is a Rock River Arms 1" Cantilever mount.  Butler Creek Scope caps are included.  They have been closed on the scope at all times unless I was looking through the scope!

Upper:  Rock River Arms Complete Upper stamped ".204 Ruger".  24" Stainless Steel Bull Barrel, and Hogue Free Float Handguard.

Lower:  Rock River Arms Complete Lower with Rock River Arms "Operator" 6-Position Stock, Ergo Sure Grip,  and Rock River Arms 2-Stage National Match Chromed Trigger

title: For Sale:   M6 Scout Hinge Pin + Retainer
postcontent:
Throw away your bolts and wing nuts.

We have milled new pins to the exact specs of the original hinge pin. We have added a hole for a steel cable to attach to your trigger guard or your barrel if you don't have the guard. Our steel pins are blued to better match the rifle and protect it from the weather. The cables are stainless steel with plastic coating to protect your rifle from scratching.

If you are going with the barrel cable, it will require a tug of the threaded end through  the center of the barrels. A layer of electrical tape and oil will pop it right through without damage to the barrels or the cable end. The excess cable can be shortened by doubling it over the end of the barrels.

The 5/16" length needed for the hole still provides a low profile unlike the bulky push pins that seem to have been the only option available for years.

Your survival rifle is only as strong as its weakest point. Lose your pin in the field and your done for the day. Don't wait until you lose yours to get your backup. We only ran 100 and will not be running any more due  to cost overruns. We're listing 50 here and 50 on Ebay.

title: For Sale:  1916 Imperial DWM 9mm Luger
postcontent:
This is a completely matching, 1916 Dated, DWM (Deutshe Waffen und Munitions Fabriken) WWI Imperial Luger with matching magazine. This is chambered for 9mm and has a standard 4" (100mm) barrel fixed sights and walnut grips. This WWI Luger manufactured for standard issue firearm to the German Military. A very unigue specimen in good condition with a lot of history in a 99 year old gun.

Serial number placement is in the Military ("exposed") style; displayed on the left side of the receiver, the side plate, the locking bolt, the sear bar safety, the extractor, the forward toggle link, the front of the frame, under the barrel, the walnut grips and the magazine. The right side of the receiver displays all the Imperial Army acceptance stamps. The original grips are finely cut diamond shaped checkering made from walnut or in some cases beech wood. These grips are serial numbered to the gun. The original firing pins were marked with the serial number and when manufactured the original grips were marked to the gun
  The extractor is marked "Geladen" on the left side and the safety is marked"Gesichert" with the safe position being downward. 

 This is a excellent example of a 1916 Dated DWM Imperial Luger with all matching. This is a difficult date to obtain in this condition.

Own a piece of history. This Luger was obtained during the Battle of The Bulge

   This is a consignment firearm. All consignment firearms are as is !!! All sales are final !!! 

We are an actual retail shop. all buyers will be required to do a background checks. We do ship to FFL's out of state. No trades!!! Contact us at REDACTED
